storyInfo: Texas needs to deliver a package from the Rat King to a bunch of old friends.

attributes.content: Penguin Logistics Lungmen Crib
Eh? Ehhh? Now this isn't right!
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: You lost.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: I'm done. This is no fun. You win every time.
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: Alright.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: Why don't we watch a movie instead.
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: Want any snacks?
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: The usual.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: You got it.
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: Here, your favorite biscuits.
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: Thanks.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: Hmm... The explosion in this scene isn't quite up to snuff. It's nowhere as good as what I put together back in school.
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: The Ursus actress playing the lead looks kinda familiar though...
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: Yeah.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: Hmm? You blew stuff up before too?
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: You could say that.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: Huh, how come you never told me about it. What's the story?
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: It's not worth talking about.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: Come on, tell me. I promise I won't tell anyone.
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: Did you blow up a school? An assembly hall? Something else, hm?
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: I think it was a tower...
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: You blew up a tower?!
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: Yeah, a tower. A leaning tower, to be precise.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: It was kinda... a landmark there.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: Whoa, I bet you didn't get out of that one easy.
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: I did it for the Family.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: Not like you, still blowing things up left and right even after you were reprimanded.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: Oh, about that.
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: School's meant to be fun. Of course I had to do the most fun thing I could possibly do.
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: Besides, I don't actually want to get anything blown up. It's just...
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: Just what?
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: I have these little accidents whenever I'm pulling my pranks...
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: Let's take that one time with Mostima for example.
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: I was just going to give her a little scare.
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: Scare who? Mostima?
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: Yeah, we went to the same school, and she was a real model student. She would give these speeches...
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: And so this one time, I installed a little spring platform on the way up to the podium, and, uh...
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: She got sprung right up?
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: Of course not. She leaped over it and got through without a scratch.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: The other girl who was right behind her wasn't so lucky, though.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: What does that have to do with blowing stuff up?
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: I'm getting to that.
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: I guess you wouldn't know, but, in Laterano, we carry guns and live rounds to these events as a show of respect.
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: And, well, it just so happens that girl was carrying a heavy weapon.
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: I'm not sure if she did that out of instinct or experience, but she fired her weapon to propel herself and land safely.
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: The thing is, there was a load-bearing column where she shot her grenade, so that blew open a corner of the assembly hall.
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: Were you really just playing a prank?
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: I was! I didn't mean to at all!
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: Hah... If you dared pull something like that in Siracusa, you would've been killed the very next day.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: Getting your head chopped off is the best deal. You hardly feel any pain that way.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: If you embarrass somebody in public, things won't be as easy.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: You might get your hands and legs chopped off, gagged, and tossed in the river—
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: Eek!
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: —They might even fish you out just to hang your corpse up on the streetcorner to warn anyone who might come up with a funny idea like you.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: Hahaha...
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: You're kidding, right...?
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: I'm not.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: Stop scaring me... I didn't know better when I was still in school. I wouldn't dare do anything like that these days!
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: Oh?
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: I'm a hardworking girl nowadays. You won't find me giving anyone any trouble.
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: It's just... sometimes... Uh...
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: I kinda wanna do something just to pull a prank on the boss. What do you think?
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: Considering how destructive your pranks get, I suggest you—
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: Oh... Bo—
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: Hyah!
attributes.name: Emperor

attributes.content: Ah!
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: Who just slapped—
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: Oh, hey, Boss. You're early today. Ahaha...
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: What? I got nothin' else to do, might as well check on my girls.
attributes.name: Emperor

attributes.content: Turns out we don't have any work now either. Haha.
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: No work? Here's something for you, then.
attributes.name: Emperor

attributes.content: Aha, here we go.
attributes.name: Emperor

attributes.content: Get your ass movin' and deliver this for me.
attributes.name: Emperor

attributes.content: Here's the address.
attributes.name: Emperor

attributes.content: Hmm...
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: Alright, I got it. I'm leaving now.
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: Texas, you go too. It's from the stinkin' old rat. You know what a pain that crusty-ass mouse is.
attributes.name: Emperor

attributes.content: Got it...
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: Come back quick. The vinyls those bitches owe me are gonna be here soon. You two are haulin' that shit for me.
attributes.name: Emperor

attributes.content: Alright.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: You can count on us!
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: Ugh, why is there a traffic jam at this time of the day?
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: It doesn't make sense.
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: Did the guys from that other company crash their street racers again?
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: Eh, Texas, you've been spacing out the whole time. Something on your mind?
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: Texas?
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: (Going by the address, this package is for the Siracusan mafia we ran into last time.)
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: (But they don't work for the Rat King anymore. Why does he want us to deliver their packages?)
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: T—e—x—a—s—
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: Huh?! What's wrong? An ambush?!
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: Nothing but cars here. No room for an ambush.
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: Sorry...
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: Hmm...
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: Texas, is this package for those guys in black we beat up a few months ago?
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: How'd you figure?
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: I mean, we're in logistics. We catch wind of lots of things on the job.
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: Whenever I deliver to that area, it's usually Lupos signing for the goods.
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: Besides, a lot of the people there hang up black hats and black jackets at home. It's not hard to tell.
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: Pretty sure they're the only ones in Lungmen who dress like that.
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: Yeah.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: Eh, Texas.
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: Hm?
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: Speaking of the mafia, I'm curious.
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: Did you used to dress like that in Siracusa?
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: Black suit and white shirt?
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: No, I wore a white tux and red shirt.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: Hm... That sounds like it could look pretty good.
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: So you didn't dress up like everyone else?
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: No, I didn't.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: What a maverick.
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: It's something the Family's key members have to do to make our power and authority known. We dressed differently from your normal Lupo lackeys.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: Doesn't that make you really stand out, though? Especially when everyone's wearing all black.
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: You sure no one's going to just—
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: Bang!
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: Off you from a distance like that?
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: Most mafia bosses are concerned about safety. They'll always have someone from the Family watching potential sniper nests.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: But if something like that does actually happen...
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: I'll slice the bolts in half myself.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: Then I'll go full damnatio memoriae on their Family. Wipe the name from Siracusa.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: Uhh...
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: Or should I say that's what I would've done?
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: These days... I guess it doesn't really matter anymore.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: It's the boss's problem to figure out how to take care of our rivals.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: All we have to do is deliver things where we're told, and maybe fight a few fights on the way. That's it.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: You have a point. Yeah, you're right.
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: Say, how long has this traffic jam been going?
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: Half an hour?
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: This isn't going to work out if we don't get moving soon.
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: Look, the driver next to us is yelling at someone already.
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: (Slams the horn repeatedly)
attributes.name: Irritated Lungmen Citizen

attributes.content: (Lowers the car's window)
attributes.name: Irritated Lungmen Citizen

attributes.content: Hey, frickin' puk gaai, get a move on already!
attributes.name: Irritated Lungmen Citizen

attributes.content: What's the rush, buddy? I'm stuck here myself.
attributes.name: Carefree Lungmen Citizen

attributes.content: Look around you. We're all in this together.
attributes.name: Carefree Lungmen Citizen

attributes.content: Yiu ah nei! If my deal gets called off, I'm gonna sau nei pei!
attributes.name: Irritated Lungmen Citizen

attributes.content: Dai lo, I'm trying to get home to the wife too, but this is a traffic jam. Ain't no one to blame for that.
attributes.name: Carefree Lungmen Citizen

attributes.content: If waiting for the cars to move ain't up to your taste, why don't we play some cards?
attributes.name: Carefree Lungmen Citizen

attributes.content: Maybe listen to the radio. News has been interesting lately.
attributes.name: Carefree Lungmen Citizen

attributes.content: (Tunes radio to the traffic channel)
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: According to reports, two vehicles were involved in a crash on the city beltway. By the time the L.G.D. has arrived on scene, the drivers had already left the scene of the accident.
attributes.name: Traffic Broadcast

attributes.content: The police are currently interviewing witnesses for descriptions of the drivers and moving the vehicles off the road. All lanes of the beltway should be open again very soon.
attributes.name: Traffic Broadcast

attributes.content: Next up, we have another traffic report—
attributes.name: Traffic Broadcast

attributes.content: That sounds kinda familiar, doesn't it, Texas?
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: Maybe we should check up on our buddies?
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: (Tunes radio channel)
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: Hello, do you copy?
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: Howdy doo, Texas?
Croissant, what's going on?
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: (Sounds of bolts flying around)
We're gettin' robbed!
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: Did your car break down?
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: Purdy sure, but I reckon we'n fix 'er up.
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: Now don't you go snitchin' on me to the baws. Wanna keep my bonus fer the month, thank'yee.
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: Got it.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: Well, I won't keep you. See you tonight.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: I thought I was the only one who'd do that.
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: You seem to do pretty well too.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: That's cause—
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: Ow!
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: Hmph...
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: If this traffic jam doesn't let up soon, Boss isn't going to be happy.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: Exusiai, I'll take the package and go on ahead. Come as soon as the highway opens up.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: Maybe I should handle the delivery.
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: Do you know what to say when you greet the mafia men?
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: Something like, 'Penguin Logistics, delivery—'
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: If you try to do that, it'll end up just as bad as that one night.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: It's a fight. I'm not scared of them.
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: Are you sure about that? They're our customers this time.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: If you are planning on beating them up and then having them sign for the package, I will say nothing more.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: Oh... right...
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: And that's why it's better that I go.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: At the very least, they are terrified of the name 'Texas,' and that will smooth most things over.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: Here's the key.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: The key? What key?
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: You want me to drive?!
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: Just for the time being.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: I'll drive on the way back.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: Alright!
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: Don't crash the car. Got it?
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: You can trust me to handle anything!
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: And I just don't...
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: *Sigh*...
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: Never mind.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: I'll see you later.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: Hm? How come Texas left her sword in the car?
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: Lungmen Markets
(Taking this alley should save me some time.)
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: (I'm almost to Kang Chai Street.)
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: (No. 8. Looks like a big warehouse. This is the place.)
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: (I hope I'll get to leave as soon as I have this delivered...)
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: No. 8, Kang Chai Street, Lungmen Markets
Hm?
attributes.name: Mafioso A

attributes.content: Texas?!
attributes.name: Mafioso B

attributes.content: S-Stop! Not a step further!
attributes.name: Mafioso A

attributes.content: (They switched to rubber arrowheads. Looks like they're starting to follow the rules.)
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: I'm only here for a delivery.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: Leave it there. We'll have someone come take it.
attributes.name: Mafioso B

attributes.content: I need to deliver it to the addressee and have it signed for. Only then can I leave.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: (Whispers) Hey, what should we do?
attributes.name: Mafioso A

attributes.content: (Whispers) Let's ask her who it's for first.
attributes.name: Mafioso B

attributes.content: We'll call the addressee and have them come out. Gimme the name.
attributes.name: Mafioso A

attributes.content: Enrico.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: Boss?!
attributes.name: Mafioso A

attributes.content: (Whispers) Hey!
attributes.name: Mafioso B

attributes.content: Uhh—*Cough*!
attributes.name: Mafioso A

attributes.content: Wait here. I'll bring Mr. Enrico out right away.
attributes.name: Mafioso A

attributes.content: (Whispers) Hang in there. I'll be back soon.
attributes.name: Mafioso A

attributes.content: T-Texas... ma'am...
attributes.name: Mafioso B

attributes.content: Hm?
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: You don't have any weapons on you, right?
attributes.name: Mafioso B

attributes.content: None at all.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: You won't pull out an Originium sword and kill us all, will you?
attributes.name: Mafioso B

attributes.content: Just like when you offed the whole Conte Family?
attributes.name: Mafioso B

attributes.content: You know the rules here. Lungmen's rules.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: Right. Yes, you're right.
attributes.name: Mafioso B

attributes.content: (Phew, thank goodness...)
attributes.name: Mafioso B

attributes.content: Mr. Enrico, this way.
attributes.name: Mafioso A

attributes.content: I'm Enrico, Signora Texas.
attributes.name: Mafia Boss

attributes.content: I heard you have something for me.
attributes.name: Mafia Boss

attributes.content: That's right. A delivery.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: It's from the Rat King. Please sign for it.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: Rat King?
attributes.name: Mafia Boss

attributes.content: Alright. Let me see it.
attributes.name: Mafia Boss

attributes.content: (Opens the package)
attributes.name: Mafia Boss

attributes.content: My...
attributes.name: Mafia Boss

attributes.content: Yes, this is from the Rat King.
attributes.name: Mafia Boss

attributes.content: Where do I sign?
attributes.name: Mafia Boss

attributes.content: Right here. On the bottom right.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: Very well—Here.
attributes.name: Mafia Boss

attributes.content: Now then—
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: Please spare me a moment, Signora Texas.
attributes.name: Mafia Boss

attributes.content: That's a title for the Family leadership back in Siracusa, not me.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: Call me Texas.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: Right, sure, Texas.
attributes.name: Mafia Boss

attributes.content: As you can see, it has been years since my brothers and I came here to Lungmen.
attributes.name: Mafia Boss

attributes.content: A while ago, Capone and Gambino got themselves pushed out of the city... they challenged the authority here, and got what came to them. That got me pushed up to lead the Family.
attributes.name: Mafia Boss

attributes.content: I want to ask your advice. If you would, please come inside for a chat.
attributes.name: Mafia Boss

attributes.content: I'm afraid I don't have much advice for you.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: I'm all ears.
attributes.name: Mafia Boss

attributes.content: Will you and your brothers ever go back to Siracusa?
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: Hoh, we'll most likely stay here in Lungmen.
attributes.name: Mafia Boss

attributes.content: There is nothing waiting for us in Siracusa. Just the Sicilian bosslady's henchmen waiting to kill us.
attributes.name: Mafia Boss

attributes.content: In that case, you might want to give up on living like a Siracusan.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: Try to live like a Lungmenite.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: Hmm...
attributes.name: Mafia Boss

attributes.content: I'm sure you know much better than anyone else whether fights between families work here.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: Whether you are from Higashi, Ursus, or Siracusa, if you want to settle down here, there is only one way.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: Be a Lungmenite.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: You aren't the first ones to come here, and you won't be the last.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: Gang members come and go. In the end, the only ones that will remain are Lungmenite.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: That's all I'm going to tell you.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: Farewell.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: Texas.
attributes.name: Mafia Boss

attributes.content: Hm?
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: Are you a Lungmenite?
attributes.name: Mafia Boss

attributes.content: Maybe.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: But I will go back one day.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: *Rattle*
*Beep*—*beep*—!
What's that sound...?
attributes.name: Mafia Boss

attributes.content: Is it coming from the box?
attributes.name: Mafia Boss

attributes.content: Hey, done already?
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: Yeah.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: I thought you'd be back by the time the road opened.
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: We had a little chat.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: I didn't know you knew how to make conversation.
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: I was just trying to keep them from giving the boss any more trouble. That's all.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: Really? Sounds like they're pretty amenable.
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: But, eh, look behind you. What's with these guys running outside?
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: Like, they're coming after you, aren't they? They don't seem very friendly to me.
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: There's a small problem...
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: I heard a noise when I was leaving. Looks like the boss made... a few modifications before handing the package over to us.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: What do we do now? Fight them?
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: Fight them? Just go!
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: This entire neighborhood is full of mafiosos. Do you want the boss to dock your pay for another car?
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: Oh, right.
attributes.name: Exusiai

attributes.content: Give me the keys. Let's go!
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: Haah—
attributes.name: Emperor

attributes.content: Eurill's a bigass cow, but he knows his wine, I'll give him that.
attributes.name: Emperor

attributes.content: Once we're done with the vinyls, Imma get a few more crates from him.
attributes.name: Emperor

attributes.content: Took your sweet time, didn't you? The vinyl damn near grew legs and walked up here.
attributes.name: Emperor

attributes.content: Wasn't the package for the mafia from the Rat King?
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: Yeah, it's the crusty rat's goods. I made a few tweaks to it.
attributes.name: Emperor

attributes.content: Those bitches in black think they can get away with blowing up my vinyl collection?
attributes.name: Emperor

attributes.content: They gonna think again.
attributes.name: Emperor

attributes.content: So, Texas, did the punks freak when they heard me rappin' after that countdown?
attributes.name: Emperor

attributes.content: None at all.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: They didn't? No way!
attributes.name: Emperor

attributes.content: I wrote this one special for those clowns. Even grabbed me a random Lupo off the street and tried it out on him before hittin' the booth. He didn't last five seconds.
attributes.name: Emperor

attributes.content: Your rap didn't knock them out. Actually, they started chasing us after a few verses.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: We drove all across Lungmen for the better part of the day just to get away from them.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: Gotta be your problem.
attributes.name: Emperor

attributes.content: I figured your average delivery time and worked it into the plan.
attributes.name: Emperor

attributes.content: I had a few extra minutes of nothin' in there when I was recording and then gave that delay button a few taps just to give you two time to get away.
attributes.name: Emperor

attributes.content: Oh, I got it.
attributes.name: Emperor

attributes.content: Did that Lupo ask you something 'cause of your name again?
attributes.name: Emperor

attributes.content: See, I thought of that. You see how my mind works?
attributes.name: Emperor

attributes.content: They got no idea. I prepped that warm-up just for them.
attributes.name: Emperor

attributes.content: After a wild, intense chase, they go home and listen to this badass tape.
attributes.name: Emperor

attributes.content: A l'il angry, and a l'il pissed.
attributes.name: Emperor

attributes.content: This is gonna keep them out of breath and snuff 'em out.
attributes.name: Emperor

attributes.content: Wei said no bullets, but he didn't say nothing about no rapping.
attributes.name: Emperor

attributes.content: Ahahahahaha.
attributes.name: Emperor

attributes.content: Uhh...
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: Now back to work. Carry those vinyls for me.
attributes.name: Emperor

attributes.content: Yes, Boss...
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: Where's Exusiai?
attributes.name: Emperor

attributes.content: She's reloading her rubber bullets.
attributes.name: Texas

attributes.content: Tell her to get a move on. The vinyls ain't waiting.
attributes.name: Emperor

attributes.content: Right...
attributes.name: Texas
